# Project-local npm config.
#
# Authenticates `npm publish` against npmjs.org via the NPM_TOKEN env var.
# npm substitutes ${NPM_TOKEN} at read time, so the secret never gets
# committed — keep it in your shell env or in .env (gitignored).
#
# Get a token at https://www.npmjs.com/settings/~/tokens — pick:
#   - "Classic Token → Automation", OR
#   - "Granular Access Token" with "Bypass two-factor authentication"
# so `npm publish` works without an OTP prompt.
//registry.npmjs.org/:_authToken=${NPM_TOKEN}
